# AI Dev Kit — Cursor Rules

## Pipeline
This project uses: /shape → /propose → /design → /implement → /review → /ship

Never write implementation code without .ai/design.md existing and approved.

## Rules

- Read TASK.md before starting any work. It contains the task brief and constraints.
- .ai/proposal.md is Gate 1 (problem + approach). Do not contradict it.
- .ai/design.md is Gate 2 (technical design). Follow it exactly.
- If .ai/design.md does not exist, do not write code. Tell the user to run /design first.
- Interview mode: code must be readable and explainable out loud. No over-engineering.
- Surface conflicts with the design rather than silently deviating.
- Do not auto-complete past a pipeline gate without user approval.

## Artifacts
- TASK.md — task brief
- .ai/proposal.md — Gate 1
- .ai/design.md — Gate 2
